Lions in the West Division final, propelling them into the Grey Cup. In a strategic move, Coach Corey Mace chose to punt with 1:48 remaining, relying on his defense to regain possession. This decision paid off, allowing quarterback Trevor Harris to lead a successful final drive, culminating in Nield's game-winning catch with only 11 seconds left. The Riders will face the Montreal Alouettes, led by undefeated quarterback Davis Alexander, in the Grey Cup.
